<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-985-698  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 985 698.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Dec 18 1989 n346 p75(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Minority-owned VAR lands Pentagon pact. (Advanced IntegratedTechnology signs contract to provide microcomputers to US Army)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Grace, Tim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Value-added reseller (VAR) Advanced Integrated Technology has wona $10 million, five-year contract to provide microcomputer-basedLANs to the US Army for use in its planning, programming, andbudgeting operations.andP;  The contract calls for a secure EthernetLAN linking 12 to 15 workstations; a systems integrator ties 30other lANs into a central server.andP;  This configuration willsimplify the Pentagon's management of databases on IBM, DEC,Sperry Corp and Wang Laboratories Inc mainframes.andP;  It uses OracleCorp's relational DBMS and DEC's DECnet-DOS communicationsprogram.andP;  Advanced Integrated Technology is a minority-owned firmwhich obtained the contract under Section 8(a) of the SmallBusiness Act and has grown 25 to 50 percent per year since joiningthe program.andP;  The company offers fourth generation language toolsand is an authorized VAR for Sun Microsystems Inc, DEC and ASTResearch Inc computers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Advanced Integrated Technology Inc. (contracts).andO;Topic:     Value-Added ResellersMilitaryDefense ContractsSmall BusinessUnited States. Army.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>